<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="563">
The 
<typeStatus>type</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. sanatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="sanatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. sanatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is rather well preserved, except for the broken antennae (the left one complete but divided in three portions, the right one missing three antennomeres in the middle) and legs (the right median leg and the hind right leg with detached tarsi). All the broken parts are glued on the label.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="563">
The specimen from NHMW, identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1883" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion sanatum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">Bembidion sanatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Netolitzky and also used by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kirschenhofer, E" journalOrPublisher="Koleopterologische Rundschau" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" pagination="57 - 92" refId="B19" refString="Kirschenhofer, E, 1984. Neue palaearktische Bembidiinae unter besonderer Beruecksichtigung der vin Eigin Suenson in Ostasien Durchgefuehrien auf Sammlungen (Col. Carabidae) 1. Teil, Bembidion Latreille. Koleopterologische Rundschau 57: 57 - 92" title="Neue palaearktische Bembidiinae unter besonderer Beruecksichtigung der vin Eigin Suenson in Ostasien Durchgefuehrien auf Sammlungen (Col. Carabidae) 1. Teil, Bembidion Latreille." volume="57" year="1984">Kirschenhofer (1984)</bibRefCitation>
in the description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirschenhofer" authorityYear="1984" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion (Peryphus) dostali" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dostali" subGenus="Peryphus">Bembidion (Peryphus) dostali</taxonomicName>
(at present assigned to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion (Peryphanes)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Peryphanes">Bembidion Peryphanes</taxonomicName>
Jeannel, 1941), as an example of the closest species, is in very bad condition: completely immature, missing almost all the appendages of the head and a part of the legs; the pronotum is evidently flattened, the elytra are open and the specimen is so immature that a dissection of the male genitalia (Kirschenhofer, 1984 mistakenly mentions this specimen as a 
<specimenCount>♀</specimenCount>
) is not recommended. The general habitus and the comparison with the 
<typeStatus>type</typeStatus>
confirmed the determination of Netolitzky.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="563">
Four of the 
<typeStatus>paratypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. dostali" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dostali">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dostali</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from NHMW are immature. The only mature male, originally glued to the label on the dorsal side, has been dissected by us and mounted again in order to leave the dorsal side visible; the specimen lacks the three left legs.
</paragraph>
